  and ... shall permitte and suffer seaven persons , by them from tyme to tyme to be elected and appointed in manner and forme aforesaid , meete and sufficiently learned to reade the said seaven lectures , to have the occupation of all my said mansion house , gardeins , and of all other thappurtenaunces , for them and every of them there to inhabite , study , and daylie to reade the said severall lectures .

architects : in 1657 he was appointed professor of astronomy at london 's gresham college

christopher wren